**Simple interest (SI)** is calculated only on the original principal, unlike compound interest which also earns interest on accumulated interest. The formula is: SI = (P × R × T) / 100, where P is principal, R is rate per year, and T is time in years. Simple interest is used in short-term personal loans and some government schemes.
